07/03/2011
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Police on Sunday (March 6th) seized 96kg of heroin at the border with Turkey in an operation co-ordinated with the US Drug Enforcement Agency. The drugs were found in a truck with Bulgarian plates transporting cement from the neighbouring country. Six people were arrested, including the suspected organisers of the trafficking channel. (Novinite, Focus, Mediapool, 24 Chasa - 06/03/11)
